<h2 id="instructions">Instructions</h2>

<p>The German mathematician Gottfried Leibniz developed the following method to approximate the value of π:</p>

<p>π/4 = 1 - 1/3 + 1/5 - 1/7 + . . .</p>

<p>Write a program that allows the user to specify the number of iterations used in this approximation and that displays the resulting value.</p>

<p>An example of the program input and output is shown below:</p>

<div class="language-text highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Enter the number of iterations: 5

The approximation of pi is 3.3396825396825403
</code></pre></div></div>

